          <pubDate>Mon, 29 Nov 2010 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
          <author>Josh Fairhead</author>
          <link>https://joshafairhead.com/tea-blog/mohokutie-second-flush-assam/</link>
          <guid>https://joshafairhead.com/tea-blog/mohokutie-second-flush-assam/</guid>
          <description xml:base="https://joshafairhead.com/tea-blog/mohokutie-second-flush-assam/">&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;https:&#x2F;&#x2F;joshafairhead.com&#x2F;tea-blog&#x2F;mohokutie-second-flush-assam&#x2F;image1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;Mohokutie Second Flush Assam packet&quot; &#x2F;&gt;
&lt;img src=&quot;https:&#x2F;&#x2F;joshafairhead.com&#x2F;tea-blog&#x2F;mohokutie-second-flush-assam&#x2F;image2.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;Tea close-up&quot; &#x2F;&gt;
Bloody good assam which has the delicacy of a Darjeeling but with more body and a strength. Most of this strength comes from the upper mids but ideally it would be a bit lower to give a more rounded taste body, consequentially it has a subtle bite to it that is only just too sharp.&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&quot;tea-details&quot;&gt;Tea Details&lt;&#x2F;h2&gt;
